  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Beginning at 14th level, the divine power that fuels your rage allows you to shrug off fatal blows.</p>\n<p>While you're @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.gaVd6MJT8Q6PLE9B]{Raging}, having 0 hit points doesn’t knock you <strong>unconscious</strong>. You still must make <strong>death saving throws</strong>, and you suffer the normal effects of taking damage while at 0 hit points. However, if you would die due to failing death saving throws, you don’t die until your rage ends, and you die then only if you still have 0 hit points.</p>",
